This paper involves the use of deep learning for image segmentation, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the focus on neural pathways and the use of high-resolution imaging data suggests that the paper may also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning for automation also suggests that the paper may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of unconventional deep learning data may suggest that the paper could also fall under the software engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
